<br>
One of the selling point for Legend's Server is better customer service and more dynamic quests. This is equivalent to hiring more full time GMs/guides.<br>
<br>
To make all servers like Legend's would most definitely mean a higher running cost, and without charging more for the extra features, VI could be making less money or even losing money and hence going out of business. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utherus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Therus</A> at: 2/8/02 10:52:52 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udelvean01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delvean01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/8/02 3:29:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My EQ Legends Journal....Some info</span><hr size=1> I think a big reason was missed for moving to Legends: annoying little kids won't be able to con their parents into paying for it. Have you been in Loio lately with an alt? Would you pay an additional 30 bucks a month to be rid of the people like you find there? I wouldn't. Its not worth it to me, but to some peope I'm sure it would be.<br>
<br>
Someone asked what things have been promised to us that we haven't gotten or content that *should* be changed to benefit ALL 400,000 PAYING players before spending time making an elite server for 8,000 people.<br>
<br>
1) The bazaar does not work as was promised it would with luclin.<br>
<br>
2) The ability to create different channels for communications in raid does not yet exist as was promised with luclin.<br>
<br>
3) When the game came out, there was 2 types of quests defined in the instructions manual. Static and dynamic. Static quests exist, but over the years dynamic GM quests have pretty much died out.<br>
<br>
4) Act of valor is broken. Holyforge and Fearless are worthless after several AAXP points. All other melee classes have useful disciplines.<br>
<br>
5) LoH as defined in the instructions manual long ago is supposed to be a complete heal. Now AAXP is needed to attain this.<br>
<br>
6) The end game is getting cramped. As some paladins like to point out, there are over 300 people in ToV some nights. Luclin encounters often don't have loot worth killing them for. Their loot or something else needs to be done to relieve some pressure in the end game.<br>
<br>
7) Some people are still having issues with running Luclin or EQ in general since luclins release.<br>
<br>
8) Customer service absolutely sucks at times. I seem to recal VI saying they would be redoing their CS department to try to make some improvements some time ago. Anyone notice any improvement?<br>
<br>
The list goes on if you just dig a little.<br>
<br>
The point is that before VI takes manpower to make the legends server, there are a lot of content issues that *should* be adressed first as they affect all of the player base and not just a select few. If the game was working as intended, I would have absolutely no problems with Legends although I would still not join. As it is, I think Legends is a slap in the face to 98% (the amount of people on the regular servers if VI gets its 8000) of VI's player base. <br>
<br>
I can see why some people are pissed by others moving to Legends, because that tells VI that it is OK for them to run it without addressing other problems first. Personally, I see that as the same as paying $12 to get rid of all ads on all EZboards versus donating to get rid of ads on on PoN. People are just looking out for themselves versus looking out for the community.<br>
<br>
As to the issue of giving everyone the same things that legends people will be getting, that can't always be done. Giving the new interface and map system to all live servers would cost VI very little as they already have it all programmed for Legends. It would be relatively simple to make it live for everyone. More dynamic quests  and better CS on the other hand, would cost more money. This is something that they would have to hire more employees for, and that is not free.<br>
<br>
Why don't I just quit if I am dissatisfied with VI? I haven't yet reached the breaking point where I feel it is not worth my 10 clams a month to continue playing. If and when VI does something to cause me to reach that point, I will quit. When enough people do so, VI will realize its mistakes and attempt to correct them. Until then, they will continue trying to maximize their profits and minimize the costs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Delvean<br>
52 paly of Brell<br>
Brell Serilis<br>
